20:23.717 --> 20:25.782
[ Music ]

21:01.354 --> 21:04.022
It's the fifth one today.

21:04.024 --> 21:06.758
- Did you call-- - They're from
an online texting site.

21:06.760 --> 21:08.460
Can you track it down?

21:08.462 --> 21:09.895
Find the IP or somethin'?

21:09.897 --> 21:11.563
It's hard to say-- maybe.

21:11.565 --> 21:12.564
I'll have to look into it.

21:12.566 --> 21:14.566
Do you have any idea who
this could be from?

21:14.568 --> 21:16.034
Well, it's hard to find
the biggest asshole

21:16.036 --> 21:18.203
in a sea full of assholes.

21:18.205 --> 21:21.306
Well, in the meantime,
maybe just think about

21:21.308 --> 21:22.942
getting your number changed.

21:22.944 --> 21:23.976
That's what I said.

21:23.978 --> 21:26.312
If I get my number changed, I'm
gonna have to tell my mom.

21:26.314 --> 21:29.015
She's gonna ask why.

21:29.017 --> 21:30.716
Look, don't respond to it.

21:30.718 --> 21:33.285
Keep track of all of them.

21:33.287 --> 21:35.955
Most of all, and I
mean this, hey.

21:35.957 --> 21:37.623
You call me if you need to.

21:37.625 --> 21:39.125
Okay?

21:51.672 --> 21:54.073
Melvin: Uh, living room here.

21:54.075 --> 21:56.375
Double doors.

21:58.212 --> 22:00.914
Kitchen here.

22:00.916 --> 22:02.482
Master bedroom.

22:04.284 --> 22:06.285
Just a closet.

22:09.022 --> 22:10.823
Uh, master bath here.

22:20.067 --> 22:21.868
Good water pressure.

22:21.870 --> 22:24.704
It-it's strong.

22:24.706 --> 22:27.140
Is there a washer
and dryer on site?

22:30.011 --> 22:31.879
What?

22:31.881 --> 22:35.983
I never believed a word those
people were sayin' about him.

22:35.985 --> 22:40.955
They strung Daniel up by the
balls, uh, if you ask me.

22:40.957 --> 22:43.958
This whole case was
just a bunch of crap.

22:43.960 --> 22:46.361
That's the way I see it.

22:46.363 --> 22:55.069
I mean, Daniel, w-we weren't...
we-we weren't close, but, uh...

22:55.071 --> 22:59.140
he was always very
nice to me, you know.

22:59.142 --> 23:01.943
Took care of my turtles.

23:01.945 --> 23:03.845
Red-eared sliders, mostly.

23:03.847 --> 23:07.882
You know, uh, when my family
would go on vacation,

23:07.884 --> 23:10.719
he would come feed 'em.

23:10.721 --> 23:16.692
You know, I always meant to go see him...
but I never did.

23:16.694 --> 23:23.133
Well... you weren't
the only one.

23:23.135 --> 23:27.671
Well, you tell him, if he needs
anything, I'm here for him.

23:27.673 --> 23:28.705
I will tell him.

23:28.707 --> 23:32.142
It's-it's Melvin.

23:32.144 --> 23:34.010
Melvin.

24:00.871 --> 24:03.465
[ Music ]

24:45.883 --> 24:50.752
[ Music ]

25:30.894 --> 25:33.412
[ Music ]

26:23.047 --> 26:33.524
♪ Sometimes I wanna take you down ♪
♪ Sometimes I wanna get you low ♪

26:33.526 --> 26:44.802
♪ brush your hair back from your eyes ♪
♪ take you down let the river flow ♪

26:44.804 --> 26:55.280
♪ sometimes I go and walk the street ♪
♪ behind the green sheet of glass ♪

26:55.282 --> 27:02.066
♪ a million miles below their feet ♪

27:14.085 --> 27:16.620
[ Thuds ]

27:18.156 --> 27:19.657
Daniel?

27:28.800 --> 27:31.835
[ Doorbell ringing ]

27:33.738 --> 27:36.840
[ Sighs ]

27:38.943 --> 27:41.412
Okay.

27:46.417 --> 27:48.252
Tawney: Hi, there!

27:48.254 --> 27:52.289
Oh... hi.

27:52.291 --> 27:54.491
Come in, come in.

28:00.531 --> 28:02.265
Um, are-are you thirsty?

28:02.267 --> 28:03.934
You want some iced tea?

28:03.936 --> 28:05.435
Oh, no, I-I can't stay.

28:05.437 --> 28:11.775
I just came to drop this by,
and maybe say hi to Daniel?

28:11.777 --> 28:14.378
Oh, yeah.

28:14.380 --> 28:16.280
He's resting.

28:16.282 --> 28:20.020
I just think the past few
days have been a lot for him.

28:21.187 --> 28:22.619
I'm sure it has.

28:22.621 --> 28:25.789
[ Squeaking in background ]

28:39.170 --> 28:45.409
Um, well, help yourself
to some monkey bread.

28:45.411 --> 28:48.445
And would you mind just
giving this card to Daniel?

28:48.447 --> 28:50.614
Absolutely.

28:54.553 --> 28:59.190
I just wanna say how
much I look up to you.

28:59.192 --> 29:00.358
Really?

29:00.360 --> 29:03.194
For what you've
done, for Daniel.

29:03.196 --> 29:05.730
I mean, nobody fought
for him like you did.

29:05.732 --> 29:08.800
And, now he's here.

29:08.802 --> 29:11.736
Out in the big, blue world.

29:16.276 --> 29:18.410
Thank you, Tawney.

29:18.412 --> 29:22.847
I don't know that I
could've stayed so strong.

29:22.849 --> 29:24.563
Well...

29:26.553 --> 29:27.886
I'll see ya later.

29:31.724 --> 29:34.825
[ Quacking ]

29:39.731 --> 29:46.981
