'cause it likes to heal ♪

29:49.753 --> 29:58.281
♪ take time with a wounded hand 'cause
it likes to heal I like to steal ♪

29:58.316 --> 30:06.847
♪ I'm half the man I used to
be this I feel as the dawn ♪

30:06.848 --> 30:11.494
♪ I'm half the man I used to be ♪

30:11.495 --> 30:16.247
♪ Half the man I used to be ♪

30:16.282 --> 30:21.053
♪ Half the man I used to be ♪

31:00.778 --> 31:03.113
This is your special mix
tape, Daniel Holden.

31:03.115 --> 31:04.815
Happy birthday.

31:04.817 --> 31:06.850
I love you, Daniel.

31:08.119 --> 31:11.669
[ Music ]

31:51.731 --> 31:53.998
- Hey.
- Hey.

31:54.000 --> 31:56.667
Uh, it's been a rough day
and I need a stiff drink.

31:56.669 --> 32:01.439
Is that even possible
in this town?

32:01.441 --> 32:04.609
Uh, sorta.

32:04.611 --> 32:07.545
Um, come pick ya up??

32:07.547 --> 32:10.715
God, yes.

32:28.935 --> 32:30.636
Hey.

32:30.638 --> 32:32.972
Hey.

32:32.974 --> 32:34.774
What you up to?

32:34.776 --> 32:38.443
About to go meet some friends.

32:38.445 --> 32:39.611
You have fun.

32:46.719 --> 32:50.088
You-you wanna come?

32:50.090 --> 32:53.125
Yeah, sure.

32:56.763 --> 32:59.865
Can't believe I thought going to
the refuge to see one baboon

32:59.867 --> 33:01.733
and a bunch of emus
was a good idea.

33:01.735 --> 33:04.937
You just wanted to spend
time with your brother.

33:04.939 --> 33:06.805
They have a baboon?

33:06.807 --> 33:09.474
If it made it through
deer huntin' season.

33:09.476 --> 33:11.877
[ Laughing ]

33:14.213 --> 33:19.752
He just... wanted to play
dress-up in dad's old clothes.

33:19.754 --> 33:21.888
Listen to his walkman.

33:21.890 --> 33:24.524
It was so sweet.

33:29.029 --> 33:30.497
We're pattin' hands now?

33:34.802 --> 33:37.805
Where are we again, besides
the middle of nowhere?

33:37.807 --> 33:40.776
The county I come from you
can sentence a man to die,

33:40.811 --> 33:42.614
but you can't buy beer.

33:42.649 --> 33:44.746
So we had to go to the next
county over for that privilege.

33:44.748 --> 33:47.215
I'm not so sure
this is good idea.

33:47.217 --> 33:48.449
Oh, it's a good idea.

33:48.451 --> 33:49.216
It's been a long week already.

33:49.218 --> 33:52.453
I need to get drunk, and
you're my designated driver.

33:52.455 --> 33:54.856
Well, you know what I mean.

33:55.258 --> 33:57.882
What about you, sailor?
How was your day?

33:57.917 --> 33:58.960
Complicated.

33:58.962 --> 34:00.995
Join the crowd, Melvin.

34:00.997 --> 34:02.330
Melvin?

34:02.332 --> 34:04.398
Not worth gettin' in to.

34:06.368 --> 34:08.302
I wanna talk to you about
something, but I don't want you to

34:08.304 --> 34:09.937
turn into the "A" train on me.

34:09.938 --> 34:12.040
I hate it when you call me that.

34:12.042 --> 34:13.841
I call you that for a reason.

34:13.842 --> 34:16.277
Okay.

34:16.279 --> 34:18.212
I won't freak out.

34:18.214 --> 34:19.947
Jared called me.

34:19.949 --> 34:22.549
Not freaking, but why?

34:22.551 --> 34:25.585
He's been getting some pretty
God awful text messages.

34:25.588 --> 34:29.989
Um, some of them about what
people wanna do to you.

34:29.992 --> 34:31.692
Like what?

34:31.694 --> 34:33.694
"Slit her throat
until she's dead"

34:33.696 --> 34:35.329
was the one that
got my attention.

34:35.331 --> 34:37.331
Well, that's graphic.

34:37.333 --> 34:39.199
Shouldn't you only
have to do that once?

34:39.202 --> 34:41.101
He called me because he
didn't wanna upset your mom.

34:41.103 --> 34:42.870
Assholes.

34:42.871 --> 34:44.972
- It doesn't scare you?
- No, it doesn't scare me.

34:44.974 --> 34:47.308
It makes me sad for
my little brother.

34:47.310 --> 34:50.011
Do you know how many prank
calls we got back then?

34:50.013 --> 34:52.746
Notes in my locker that said, "I'll give
you something to choke on, bitch."

34:52.748 --> 34:53.848
This isn't new.

34:53.850 --> 34:55.183
Daniel being out is.

34:55.185 --> 34:57.318
I've been through it.

34:57.320 --> 35:01.489
I just didn't want Jared to
have to go through it, too.

35:01.491 --> 35:04.359
And then, he has to
hide it from everybody.

35:04.361 --> 35:06.027
What a family.

35:08.597 --> 35:11.666
Amantha, you're gonna
have to pull it together.

35:11.668 --> 35:13.368
I know, Jon.

35:13.370 --> 35:15.070
It's just that being back here
is bringing up a shitload

35:15.072 --> 35:19.809
of old feelings... and that's why
I've been a tad clingy of late.

35:22.846 --> 35:28.217
Not to mention the fact that I'm
very fond of you, Jon Stern.

35:28.219 --> 35:32.287
And I'm very fond of you,
too, Amantha Holden.

35:32.289 --> 35:35.991
And I know that attraction
is, partly, because of

35:35.993 --> 35:40.529
our common interest, my brother,
the center of our universe.

35:40.531 --> 35:46.068
- But, damn it--
Bobby Dean: - Can I buy you a drink?

35:52.943 --> 35:58.447
No... thank you.

35:58.449 --> 36:00.883
Your brother moving back here?

36:02.386 --> 36:03.987
I don't know.

36:06.456 --> 36:12.428
Um, I don't-I don't know
his permanent plans.

36:12.430 --> 36:14.163
I don't know.

36:21.171 --> 36:22.972
See ya 'round.

36:26.743 --> 36:29.178
What the hell was that about?

36:29.180 --> 36:31.547
We have to go.

36:34.884 --> 36:36.986
Well?

36:36.988 --> 36:41.023
It's Hannah's brother...
all grown up.

36:41.025 --> 36:41.591
What?

36:41.593 --> 36:44.260
Little Bobby Dean.

36:45.662 --> 36:47.697
I watched Daniel
go to death row.

36:47.699 --> 36:52.601
He buried his sister, and then, we
went to algebra class together.

36:52.603 --> 36:56.105
You're just too young and
too in the middle of it

36:56.107 --> 36:58.674
to know how crazy it
all was at the time.

37:00.811 --> 37:04.146
You know he's messed up.

37:06.617 --> 37:10.553
Jon, I need you to
take me somewhere.

37:25.800 --> 37:31.305
You see that patch of trees
right there, behind the rocks?

37:31.307 --> 37:39.914
That's where, uh... I haven't been
out here in such a long time.

37:39.916 --> 37:42.015
My God.

37:53.829 --> 37:59.967
After it was all over, the trial
and everything, and Daniel was

37:59.969 --> 38:05.306
sentenced to die, it became
pretty taboo to come out here.

38:05.308 --> 38:10.245
But you know kids, we broke
that one pretty quick.

38:10.247 --> 38:17.318
In a few years, it had become
this macabre rite of passage.

38:17.320 --> 38:19.954
I didn't know about it at the
time, for obvious reasons,

38:19.956 --> 38:23.158
but the older teenagers would
bring the younger teenagers

38:23.160 --> 38:25.893
out here... always at night.

38:25.895 --> 38:29.297
And they would tell this story
of this boy named Daniel

38:29.299 --> 38:31.132
and this girl named Hannah.

38:31.134 --> 38:34.135
Now, Daniel had wanted to
have sex with Hannah,

38:34.137 --> 38:38.206
but Hannah was a virgin and wanted
to save herself for marriage.

38:38.208 --> 38:44.646
Daniel did it to her anyway... even
though Hannah begged him not to.

38:44.648 --> 38:51.686
And then, he said they would get
married now, and he consummated it

38:51.688 --> 38:56.825
by strangling her to death and
covering her body with wildflowers.

38:56.827 --> 39:00.095
Just as an older teenager was
finishing telling the morbid tale,

39:00.097 --> 39:03.865
and you could hear a pin
drop in a car full of kids,

39:03.867 --> 39:06.334
other teenagers who had
been hidin' would suddenly

39:06.336 --> 39:09.004
bang on all the car windows.

39:09.006 --> 39:11.639
Kids would pee their pants.

39:11.641 --> 39:16.377
[ Sighs ]

39:16.379 --> 39:21.249
How did you find out about this?

39:21.251 --> 39:22.984
My best friend told me.

39:25.087 --> 39:29.790
She had come out here one night.
Felt guilty about it.

39:29.792 --> 39:33.127
Said she'd been hanging on to
her secret for over a year

39:33.129 --> 39:34.161
before she finally confessed.

39:34.163 --> 39:38.255
I made her come out here and
go through the whole thing.

39:38.290 --> 39:40.034
You know me.

39:40.036 --> 39:45.707
She cried a lot, but she did it.

39:45.709 --> 39:47.776
What happened to her?

39:47.778 --> 39:51.712
I don't know.

39:51.714 --> 39:55.283
I never talked to her again
after that-- not one word.

39:55.285 --> 39:57.251
You know me.

39:59.321 --> 40:01.956
I've been thinking about
her a lot lately.

40:04.760 --> 40:08.329
Jenny Park.

40:08.331 --> 40:10.431
You could get in touch
with her, you know?

40:10.433 --> 40:13.201
It's not too late.

40:13.203 --> 40:16.438
Yeah... I guess.

40:19.876 --> 40:25.788
[ Music ]

40:27.819 --> 40:30.120
Amantha?

40:33.258 --> 40:35.707
[ Music ]

41:12.701 --> 41:14.836
Daniel?

41:14.838 --> 41:16.938
Hey.

41:19.975 --> 41:22.376
It's got your name on it.

41:24.413 --> 41:26.414
Come on-- why not?

